      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لَهُ سَمَكَةٌ اِرْتَفَعَتْ فَوَقَعَتْ عَلَى اَلْجَدَدِ فَاضْطَرَبَتْ حَتَّى مَاتَتْ آكُلُهَا قَالَ \"نَعَمْ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4155 - Aban narrated from Zurara who said: I asked him about a fish that leaps out of the water, falls onto dry land, and struggles until it dies.\nI said: \"Can I eat it?\"\nImam (as) said: \"Yes.\""
        ]
      }
